data.event: The species of oak that grows in this area is Quercus robur L. In its earliest days Dubrava was no more than a village, consisting of a couple of houses and gardens.

event.title: the 1930s Dubrava had over hundred inhabitants and was connected

data.event: By the 1930s Dubrava had over hundred inhabitants and was connected with Zagreb via road.

Because of many victims of partisan bombing of public and military targets, army was sent to Dubrava and after investigations and skirmishes with partisans, the Army of the Independent State of Croatia hanged 13 partisans on December 1944.

data.event: Later, these were termed "national heroes" and a monuments were built in their honor in the Park of December Victims and on the corner of the Konjščinska Street.
